FBIS4-62541 "drsov095_v_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-095 Daily Report 13 May 1994 Lithuania Premier Meets Health Leaders; Minister Notes Debt Problem Premier Meets Health Leaders; Minister Notes Debt Problem WS1605125694 Vilnius ELTA in English 1835 GMT 13 May 94 WS1605125694 Vilnius ELTA English BFN [From "News Bulletin" No. 499] [Text] Vilnius, 13 May, ELTA -- Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius met leaders of health organizations on Thursday [12 May] and talked about threatening economic situation of Lithuanian health care. Health Minister Jurgis Bredikis told a news conference on Friday that hospitals were overburdened by huge debts. Six million Litas are unpaid by them only for municipal services. There is a great lack of medicines, equipment, dressing, clothes and other necessary things in hospitals. Bredikis said 9 million Litas were still not transferred from the budget for the needs of the health system. Bredikis also said that, because of difficult economic situation and before creating the medical insurance system, an amount of paid medical services would be increased.
